<HEADLINE> Jospin to Attend First Match by French Team in World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
will attend the first World Cup football match by the French team
against South Africa to be held on June 12 in Marseille.
</P>
<P>
French officials said that Jospin will be accompanied by the
Minister of Justice Elisabeth Guigou and Interior Minister
Jean-Pierre Chevenement to watch the match in the Velodrome
Stadium in downtown Marseille.  
</P>
