<HEADLINE> French Appeal Court to Hold Hearing on Diana Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Court of Appeal of Paris will ban
photographers and all cameramen from the hearing to be organized
Friday on the death of Princess Diana, said Agence France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
The president of the court said that the decision was made at
the request of all the parties involved in the case.
</P>
<P>
A dozen witnesses will be present at the hearing for
cross-examinations by judges.
</P>
<P>
Among them will be Mohamed al-Fayad, the father of Diana's
lover Dodi and the owner of the Ritz Hotel in Paris.
</P>
<P>
Princess Diana was killed in the mid-night of August 31, 1997,
in a car crash under the Alma tunnel in central Paris.  
</P>
</TEXT>
