<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> P-5 FMs Meet to Defuse Tension in South Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers of the five
permanent members of the Security Council (P-5) began their
meeting here Thursday evening on the situation in South Asia
following the recent nuclear testing by India and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is aimed at "seeking ways to defuse tension in
South Asia resulting from the nuclear tests conducted by India and
Pakistan," said Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan in his
opening remarks.
</P>
<P>
China is the current rotating coordinator of the P-5. Others
present at the P-5 meeting at the foreign minister level are
Yevgeny Primakov of Russia, Hubert Vedrine of France, Madeleine
Albright of the United States and Robin Cook of Britain.
</P>
<P>
"At present, peace and stability in South Asia is being gravely
undermined and the international non-proliferation regime is faced
with a critical test," Tang said.
</P>
<P>
"It is thus all the more imperative for the Permanent Five to
demonstrate strong political will, and, in the interest of peace
and stability in which we share a common stake, explore ways to
reverse the nuclear arms race in South Asia, consolidate the
international non-proliferation regime and prevent the escalation
of tension in South Asia," he said.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday morning, Tang held bilateral consultations with
Primakov and Albright respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
