<HEADLINE> Striking Air France Pilots Near Deal with Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The biggest union of striking pilots
of Air France, the SNPL, said Thursday afternoon that they are
nearing a deal with the company's management.
</P>
<P>
But the SNPL refused to confirm reports that the pilots were
ready to accept a reduction of their salaries in exchange for
obligation for the shares of the company in a limited period of
time, the major dispute between the pilots and the management.
</P>
<P>
The pilots and the management will resume full talks this
evening and are expected to reach a deal after four days of strike
that greatly paralyzed the long-haul flights of Air France and
forced the company to cancel from 60 to 70 percent of the short
and medium-haul flights.
</P>
<P>
All French political leaders have called on the two sides to
reach an agreement as soon as possible, with the World Cup
football finals only being six days away.  
</P>
</TEXT>
