<HEADLINE> New Hungarian National Assembly to Be Inaugurated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The new National Assembly of
Hungary will be inaugurated on June 18, Hungarian President Goncy
Arpad announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The parties which won the legislative elections will begin
negotiations on preparation work for the inauguration, on June 9.
</P>
<P>
Six parties won seats in the 386-seat unicameral National
Assembly in the two rounds of legislative elections held on May 10
and 24.
</P>
<P>
They are the Federation of Young Democrats (Fidesz-MPP), the
Socialist Party, the Small Holder's Party, the Hungarian
Democratic Party, the Alliance of Free Democrats, and the Party of
Hungarian Life and Justice.
</P>
<P>
Arpad has said that Fidesz-MPP chief Orban Viktor will be
authorized to form the new cabinet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
