<HEADLINE> France to Sell Russia 3 Telecommunications Satellites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The French telecommunications group
Alcatel and the aeronautics group Aerospatiale will deliver three
telecommunications satellites to Russia under a contract signed
with the Russian government.
</P>
<P>
A communique by Alcatel and Aerospatiale, which cooperated with
the Russian space industrial group NPO-PM in this project, said
that the Express K satellites will be used to renew Russia's
telecommunications satellites network.
</P>
<P>
"These satellites will be of a power at least five times
greater than the present models in Russia, and will offer services
in telephone, fax and transmission of documents over the whole
territory of the Russian federation," it said.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed during recent visit by Russian Prime
Minister Sergei Kiriyenko in Paris.  
</P>
