<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hamas Warns Against Israeli Barring Yassin's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A leader of the militant Islamic
resistance movement Hamas Thursday warned Israel not to bar its
founder Sheikh Ahmed Yassin from returning to the Palestinian
self-rule area, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Mahamoud Azahar, Hamas leader in Gaza Strip, told reporters
that if Israel does not allow Yassin to return, there will be a
new wave of violence.
</P>
<P>
He said that he would like to remind Israel how many soldiers
were kidnaped and killed by Hamas to gain Yassin's release from
jail.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai said Wednesday that
Yassin could be barred from returning to Gaza following his
regional tour and that the issue is now under discussion.
</P>
<P>
Yassin, also the spiritual leader of Hamas, was released from
Israeli jail last October after serving 10 years of a life
sentence for ordering the killing of Palestinians who collaborated
with Israel.
</P>
<P>
Since his release, Yassin has repeatedly called on Palestinians
to intensify their fight against Israel. He currently is visiting
Arab and Islamic states and raising funds for Hamas.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, a Palestinian court in Gaza has
order the release of Abdel Aziz Rantisi, Hamas spokesman in Gaza.
</P>
<P>
Rantisi was arrested two months ago after he blamed the
Palestinian National Authority for involvement in the death of
Hamas chief bomb-maker Mohei Eddine Sharif. 
</P>
</TEXT>
