<HEADLINE> Cypriots Urged to Protect Marine Ecosystems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Cypriot Minister of Agriculture,
Natural Resources and Environment Costas Themistocleous Thursday
stressed the need for protecting Cyprus' seas and the ecosystems.
</P>
<P>
In a message to mark the International Environment Day Friday,
Themistocleous said this year's theme - protection of the ocean -
is especially important for Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
"We must concentrate our efforts on keeping our seas pure and
clean and as a consequence safeguard the functioning of the
coastal and marine ecosystems," he added.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that protecting the environment depends on
balanced and correct development, noting that this factor has a
special importance to Cyprus, where the division of the island has
increased environmental problems.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has remained divided since 1974, when Turkey landed its
troops and took over the northern third of the Mediterranean
island to protect the Turkish Cypriot minorities, after a coup by
Greek Cypriots seeking union with Greece. 
</P>
</TEXT>
