<DOCNO> XIE19980605.0039 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> P5 Foreign Ministers Issue Joint Communique on South Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers of the five
permanent members of the Security Council (P5) pledged to
cooperate closely in urgent efforts to prevent a nuclear and
missile arms race in South Asia in a joint communique issued at
the end of their one-day meeting here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was chaired by Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan, the current rotating coordinator of the P5. Others
present at the P5 meeting at the foreign minister level are
Evegueni Primakov of Russia, Hubert Vedrine of France, Mrs
Madeleine Albright of the United States and Robin Cook of the
United Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
They met to coordinate their response to the grave situation
created by the nuclear tests carried out last month by India and
then by Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
In the communique, the ministers "condemned these tests,
expressed their deep concern about the danger to peace and
stability in the region, and pledged to cooperate closely in
urgent efforts to prevent a nuclear and missile arms race in the
subcontinent, to bolster the non-proliferation regime, and to
encourage reconciliation and peaceful resolution of differences
between India and Pakistan".
</P>
<P>
The ministers urged India and Pakistan to stop all further
nuclear tests and to refrain from the weaponization or deployment
of nuclear weapons, from the testing or deployment of missiles
capable of delivering nuclear weapons, and from any further
production of fissile material for nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
They called on Indian and Pakistan to adhere to the
Comprehensive Nuclear Test Ban Treaty (CTBT) immediately and
unconditionally.
</P>
<P>
The P5 will seek firm commitments by India and Pakistan not to
weaponize or deploy nuclear weapons or missiles. They agreed that
the international non-proliferation regime must remain strong and
effective despite the recent nuclear tests in South Asia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980605.0040 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
