the junta supporters, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Remnants of the military junta led by Johnny Paul Koromah has
recently, according to media reports, turned to terrorists actions
against civilians, as hundreds of people have had their hands, feet
and other body parts crudely amputated.
</P>
<P>
The junta forces, driven out Freetown in February by the west
African peace-keeping force ECOMOG, have run short of ammunitions and
supplies, said ECOMOG commander, Major-General Timothy Shelpidi in
Lagos Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Complaining that rains are slowing down ECOMOG's operations to mop
up remnants of the junta forces nationwide, Shelpidi called on the
international society to provide logistics support to ECOMOG. 
</P>
