<HEADLINE> Renewable Energy Helpful to Meet Greece's Energy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Greece will be able to cover 20
percent of its energy requirements if it uses renewable sources
such as water, aeolic and solar energy, the environmental
organization Greenpeace said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Stelios Psomas, head of
Greenpeace's Greek branch, said that adoption of the
organization's proposal for using renewable energy would help
lessen reliance on conventional fuel and reduce air pollution.
</P>
<P>
The Greenpeace proposed that Greece should make institutional
and legislative changes to promote the exploitation of renewable
energy sources, to allocate public land for related investments,
to make incentives for consumers to use renewable energy, to set
an example by the public sector through its use of such sources in
public buildings and to brief consumers and productive classes on
forthcoming developments in the energy sector.
</P>
<P>
The organization stressed that Greece was in the advantageous
position of having enormous potential in all sources of renewable
energy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
