<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980605.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former US Pilot Traces Wartime Savior </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Rex Barber, an 80-year old
former American pilot, has traced the Chinese boy who rescued him
when he was shot down near here in World War Two.
</P>
<P>
Barber's fighter plane was shot down by a Japanese plane over
Dongting Lake in Central China's Hunan Province one day in
April 1944, and his life was saved by two Chinese boys.
</P>
<P>
For the past five decades Barber had always dreamed of finding
his Chinese saviors. Last April, he turned to Chinese news media
in the United States for help.
</P>
<P>
The old man, now living in Oregon State, told the newsmen that
when he parachuted from his stricken plane he broke both ankles
and both knees. Two Chinese teenagers helped him to hide from
pursuing Japanese soldiers.
</P>
<P>
When the Hunan provincial government learned about the story, it
set up special groups in Yueyang, Yiyang and Changde cities to
search for the boys.
</P>
<P>
The local government of Yueyang County found that a 66-year-old
farmer named Rong Zhizhou was one of Barber's saviors.
</P>
<P>
In April this year, Barber asked a friend named Dr. Ye to come
to China to see Rong.
</P>
<P>
Rong recollected how he and Shao Huangsheng, who has since
died, helped Barber to escape from the danger. These details were
confirmed by Barber.
</P>
<P>
Rong said that he and Shao were playing on the bank of Dongting
Lake near Rongjiawan Railway Station, when they saw an airplane
crash, and afterwards a huge "umbrella" with a foreign man falling
down.
</P>
<P>
Rong said that they guessed that the injured pilot must be a
foreigner helping the Chinese to fight the Japanese invaders.
</P>
<P>
"We hid him in the reeds beside the lake side, and that way he
escaped being found by the Japanese soldiers," he said.
</P>
<P>
Rong and Shao then got some other people to carry the pilot to
a township office, where a doctor gave him treatment.
</P>
<P>
When Barber learned the details from Dr.Ye, he confirmed that
Rong and Shao were his saviors.
</P>
<P>
In a letter he wrote which arrived in Yueyang County yesterday,
Barber said that he and his family are looking forward to meeting
Rong in future and nothing can express his sincere gratitude to
the two Chinese boys.  
</P>
</TEXT>
