<HEADLINE> "Vegetable Basket Project" Provides Ample Supply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese urbanites are now having
ample supply of vegetables at reasonable price, as the national
"Vegetable Basket Project" is bearing fruits.
</P>
<P>
According to today's People's Daily, the annual vegetable
output value of the country has amounted to 250 billion yuan
(30.12 billion US dollars), becoming the second money contributor
only after grain to the agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
At present, the China's per capita annual vegetable consumption
has reached 253 kg, more than double the figure of 119
kg 12 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The vegetable production structure has already shifted from the
traditionally "family garden type" into a mass production style.
</P>
<P>
Technology has helped increase the use of green house growing
and the variety hybridization. The operation of high technology
content has dramatically pushed up the income of vegetable growers.
</P>
<P>
However, the Daily points out, the sector is still confronted
with problems and challenges such as the incongruity between the
comparatively small-scale production and the big market and the
problem of regional and seasonal oversupply.
</P>
<P>
"The vegetable market is basically a buyers' market;" the Daily
warns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
