<HEADLINE> Japan Steps up to Ninth at Women's Basketball World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Japan, 12th place finisher four
years ago in Sydney, surged to ninth place as the Asian runner-up
trounced Hungary 108-82 in a classification game for 9-10 at the
Women's World Basketball Championship here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Center Noriko Hamaguchi paced Japan, also seventh in the
women's basketball tournament in Atlanta in 1996, with 24 points
while both forward Mikiko Hagiwara, who played in WNBA in the
United States last year, and guard Chikako Murakami tossed in 15
points apiece.
</P>
