<HEADLINE> S. African Exports of Vehicles Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Exports of South
African-produced vehicles rose more than 66 percent in the first
four months this year to 8,524 units compared with 5,123 units
last year.
</P>
<P>
A survey by the National Association of Automobile
Manufacturers Association showed that passenger vehicle exports
were the only contributor to this increase, rising by more than
160 percent from 2,287 units last year to 5,986 this year.
</P>
<P>
By contrast, exports of South African-made light, medium and
heavy commercial vehicles have declined in this period compared
with last year.
</P>
<P>
light commercial vehicle exports dropped by 8.3 percent to
2,329 units from 2,541 last year while medium and heavy
commercial vehicle exports slumped by 29.2 percent to 209 units
this year from 295 units last year.
</P>
<P>
Exports of South African-produced vehicles last year totaled
19,569 units compared with 11,553 vehicles exported in 1996.
</P>
