<HEADLINE> Zambia to Evacuate Forsaken Women From W. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government is to
evacuate scores of its female nationals stranded in west Africa
after being abandoned by their husbands.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by Zambian Foreign Minister Keli Walubita
Thursday in Mali on his way to Burkina Faso for the annual summit
of the Organization for African Unity (OAU), the Times of Zambia
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Moved by the plight of Zambian women who once married to west
African dealers in emeralds and other precious stones, Walubita
said the Zambian government has already started a program of
locating Zambians living abroad, especially those stranded in
west Africa, so that meaningful assistance can be given to them
in times of difficulty.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister added that Zambians living in foreign
countries have been asked to register at nearest Zambian
embassies or high commissions.
</P>
<P>
He said his ministry has already established a unit directly
responsible for this task, adding that it was high time the
Zambians abroad started benefiting from the goodwill of their
government.
</P>
<P>
A number of Zambian women are currently stranded in Senegal,
Mali, Cote d'Ivoire and Nigeria. They were lured to these
countries by the fantastic amounts of money which their husbands
were realizing from sales of precious stones, said the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The official number of the Zambian women living in Mali is
estimated at 30, although the actual figure could be higher. All
the women are married to the Malians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
