murder cases show that blacks convicted of murder are far more
likely to be sentenced to death than others who commit similar
crimes.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- Factory orders gained 1.2 percent in April, climbing for the
fourth time in five months. Manufactures' inventories also rose.
Economics differ on whether the buildup reflects slow sales or
plans for future prices or demand.
</P>
<P>
USA Today:
</P>
