<HEADLINE> Nation Urged To Promote Science, Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The whole nation should give more
importance to the strategy of revitalizing China through science
and education, said a senior Chinese leader today.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing made the remark at the closing ceremony
of a five-day conference attended by members of the Chinese
Academy of Sciences (CAS) and the Chinese Academy of Engineering
(CAE).
</P>
<P>
"To solve our problem of feeding more than one billion people
with a shrinking amount of farmland, scientific renovations and
technological improvements must be fully stressed," said Li, also
a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau of the
Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
He urged leading officials at all levels to take concrete steps
to boost economic growth by means of knowledge, and give full
support to efforts to boost science and education.
</P>
<P>
He said that research should better serve the needs of social
and economic development, and that the pace of the transfer of
scientific findings into social and economic benefits should be
stepped up.
</P>
<P>
Stressing the importance of younger talented people, Li also
asked the veteran members of both CAS and CAE to create more
chances for and give more help to the younger generation. 
