<HEADLINE> Philippine Airlines Pilots Go on Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Pilots of Philippine Airlines (PAL)
began a strike here Friday night over a dispute with the
management, causing the delay or cancellation of many flights.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Airlines in a press release called the strike
illegal and in open defiance of two orders of the Department of
Labor and Employment which has already assumed jurisdiction over
the dispute.
</P>
<P>
The airlines management apologized to the riding public for the
inconvenience caused by the untimely disruption of its operations.
It said it would strive to mount as many flights as possible.
</P>
<P>
The major reason for the current standoff is the case of Airbus
300 Captain Albino Collantes, whom the PAL management opted to
retire last year after he completed the minimum requirement of 20
years service with the company.
</P>
<P>
In two orders issued earlier, the Office of the Labor Secretary
warned the pilots against undertaking any action that would
exacerbate the situation. 
</P>
