<HEADLINE> CAS, CAE Appoint Senior Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- One hundred and forty-five old
scientists and 30 entineering experts were appointed today as
senior members of the Chinese Academy of Sciences(CAS) and the
Chinese Academy of Engineering (CAE), respectively.
</P>
<P>
Qian Xueshen, the forerunner of China's space technology, and
other 10 people accepted the senior membership from both CAS and
CAE.
</P>
<P>
They are the first group of senior members of China's top
scientific and technological research bodies which will formally
put in place the senior membership system as of July
1st. Under the system, CAS and CAE Academicians of 80 years
old will automatically acquire senior membership.
</P>
<P>
According to a CAS official, the new system is adopted in line
with the same practise in some foreign countries and with a view
to better protecting the health of old academicians.
</P>
<P>
The senior members can work as consultants and take part in
academic appraisal and academic exchanges, though they should not
stay in the leadership posts or participate in nominating
candidates of and electing CAS and CAE members, the official said.
</P>
<P>
CAS and CAE will set up a special fund that will provide each
senior member with a stipend of 10,000 yuan (about 1,200 US
dollars) a year, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
