city on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Paris will organize a spectacular celebration on June 9, the
eve of the opening of the World Cup, with processions headed by
20-meter and 38-ton "giants" moving from four sectors of the city
to converge on the Concorde Place in central Paris.
</P>
<P>
The celebration will reach the climax with rock music and
performances by 800 costumed artists throughout the night, which
is expected to be attended by more than 80,000 people.
</P>
<P>
