<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3,563 Khmer Rouge Defectors Join Royal Troops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANLONG VENG, Cambodia, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A total of 3,563
breakaway Khmer Rouge troops were integrated into the Royal
Cambodia Armed Forces (RCAF) Friday, at Anlong Veng, a former
stronghold of the Khmer Rouge.
</P>
<P>
At an integration ceremony, Co-Minister of Defense Tea Banh
said, "From now on, we could say that Cambodia has got rid of the
war, which caused a lot of suffering to the country and people,
and peace has been realized.
</P>
<P>
"It would benefit a lot our country's reconstruction and
development in the future. The Royal Government of Cambodia will
do its best to help soldiers and civilians in Anlong Veng to
overcome the difficulties they are facing from now on," he said.
</P>
<P>
At Anlong Veng, the 3,563 officers and soldiers, defected from
Khmer Rouge's thirteen divisions and donned new RCAF uniforms on
spot. They were integrated into the Fourth Military Region of the
RCAF.
</P>
<P>
Government officials, high-ranking officers, military attaches
and journalists witnessed the integration ceremony.
</P>
<P>
In March, about 1,000 Khmer Rouge troops in Anlong Veng
mutinied, delivering the rebels' headquarters for military
operations since 1990 into government hands. Other mass defections
from Preah Vihear and Siem Reap provinces in March helped cripple
the guerrilla movement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
