<HEADLINE> Three Killed in Bomb Blast in Eastern Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Three persons were killed and one
injured Friday afternoon when a bomb exploded at a local cinema in
Lahore, capital of Pakistan's eastern Punjab province, the
official APP reported.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said the bomb was concealed under a seat in the
upper gallery of the cinema located next to a police station in
Lahore, about 300 kilometers southeast of Islamabad, said the
Associated Press of Pakistan (APP).
</P>
<P>
"The bomb went off with a bang 15 minutes after the show began.
Fortunately there were only 10 persons sitting in the gallery,"
APP quoted a bewildered eyewitness as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the police have taken three cinema employees into
custody for interrogation, APP said, adding that more details were
awaited. 
</P>
</TEXT>
