<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Italians Scale Mount Dhaulagiri </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Two Italians have scaled the
8,167-meter Mount Dhaulagiri from the northeast ridge route, the
Nepal Tourism Ministry said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Tarcisio Bello 36, and Mario Vielmo, 35, members of a
seven-men Italian squad, reached the summit on May 26.
</P>
<P>
Mount Dhaulagiri is the world's seventh tallest peak. It has
claimed the lives of 33 climbers, including five Americans and
three Nepalese in the Autumn of 1969. 
</P>
</TEXT>
