<HEADLINE> Chinese Academy of Engineering Elects Foreign Academicians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Five foreign scientists were
elected as the second batch of foreign academicians of the Chinese
Academy of Engineering (CAE) here today.
</P>
<P>
Pan Jiazheng, vice-president of the CAE, announced the namelist
today at the biennial Conference of the Academicians of the
Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS) and the CAE.
</P>
<P>
The five foreign academicians were French molecular biologist
Pierre Tiollais, U.S. mineral processing expert P. Somasundaran,
Russian scientist V. N. Pochukaev, U.S. microelectronics expert
Simon M. Sze, and British plant genome researcher Michael Denis
Gale.
</P>
<P>
The five foreign academicians were all authoritative figures in
the study of a special field, and have maintained close
cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of seven CAE foreign academicians were elected
in June 1996, when the Third CAE Academicians Conference was
held. 
</P>
</TEXT>
