<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 128.32 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the Bombay
Stock Exchange (BSE) market lost 128.32 points to 3417.89 as
against Thursday's close of 3546.21.
</P>
<P>
The national index also went down by 63.26 points to 1513.94
from the previous close of 1577.2.
</P>
<P>
Equities crashed on the last day of the current settlement
bringing the sensitive index sharply down by more than 128 points
on the BSE market Friday on heavy bull liquidation and continued
selling pressure by foreign funds induced by Moody's warning about
the downward pressure on India's ratings.
</P>
<P>
The market took seriously a warning by Moody's investor service
that downward pressure on India's ratings has intensified due to
international sanctions imposed on the country after its nuclear
tests and lack of substantive measures in the 1998-99 budget to
attract foreign investments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
