<HEADLINE> World Bank to Fund Hunan Power Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan Province
will use 300 million US dollars in loans from the World Bank for
the improvement of the local power industry.
</P>
<P>
This will be the largest loan ever introduced by the province
from the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
Part of the 20-year loan will be used for the second phase
of construction of the Leiyang Power Plant in the southern
part of the province, which is expected to install two 300,000-kw
generating units.
</P>
<P>
The Furong Substation in this provincial capital will use the
rest of the loans to purchase cables and other types of electrical
equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
