<HEADLINE> Bank of China Explores World Credit Card Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC), the
nation's biggest foreign exchange bank, is actively exploring the
world credit card market, aiming to basically establish its own
card network in two years.
</P>
<P>
The bank plans to issue credit cards in New York this year, and
finish the feasibility study for issuing cards in Europe, as an
important step in its globalization effort. Hong Kong is expected
to become the processing center of the global network.
</P>
<P>
The BOC has already issued cards in Singapore (20,000 cards),
London and Sidney.
</P>
<P>
The bank issued a total of its 340,000 Great Wall cards in
1997, up 13 percent from 1996. It also issued 2.58 million Great
Wall Electronic Debit Cards, with a total transaction turnover of
12.2 billion yuan; its designated agents surpassed 61,800, an
increase of 17 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
The bank also plans to kick start a series of measures this
year, to upgrade the technological level of the credit card
network and increase the efficiency of its credit card service.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
