<HEADLINE> 500,000 Indians Die of TB Every Year: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 5 (Xinhua) -- India's Health and Family Welfare
Minister Dalit Ezhilmalai said Friday that about 500,000 people in
the country die of tuberculosis (TB) every year.
</P>
<P>
In a written reply to a question in the Upper House of
Parliament here, Ezhilmalai said that at present there are about
14 million patients suffering from TB in the country.
</P>
<P>
He said the government has formulated a revised strategy for
effective control of TB and the objective of the strategy is to
achieve an over 85 percent cure rate as against the existing rate
of about 30 percent. 
</P>
