<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Confiscates Illicit Explosives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A nationwide swoop by the police
since the beginning of this year has netted a large batch of
explosives held illegally.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from a dozen provinces and municipalities show that
by mid-May the police had inspected some 17,000 manufactures,
traders and users of explosives, and found 2,700 potential
problems.
</P>
<P>
As a result, they sent notices to more than 1,400 units,
ordering them to solve those problems within a specified
time. Meanwhile, they revoked the licenses of another 110
units found guilty of serious breaches of the law.
</P>
<P>
A senior police officer said that although all units with
connections with explosives are on the inspection list, attention
was focused on small mines and quarries.
</P>
<P>
He said that the inspectors confiscated 196 tons of dynamite,
310,000 detonators and 300,000 m of fuse. They also closed down
577 unlicensed explosives manufacturers and 1,200 traders, and
punished 1,272 people involved.
</P>
<P>
The inspection concentrated on whether the units had proper
licenses to manufacture, trade in or utilize the explosives,
whether storehouses met the safety requirements, and whether the
related staff had received proper training and obtained
certificates of competence.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980605.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Still Attraction for Foreign Investment: Salvador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The burgeoning China market should
not be ignored by any far-sighted foreign investor, said Aldo
Salvador, president of the Franco-China Chamber of Commerce and
Industry.
</P>
<P>
Salvador, who is also the chief representative of France's
Rhone-Poulenc China Ltd, told Xinhua today that China still enjoys
good potential for further economic growth, as the government's
reform policies are taking effect in all walks of life here.
</P>
<P>
Regarded as an "island of safety" in the Asian financial
crisis, China will survive the ``temporary difficulties" caused by
the negative external environment, and then enter a new round of
rapid development, he said.
</P>
<P>
As a reflection of the Chinese government's outstanding
performance in leading the country's economic take-off over the
past five years, China has achieved an annual economic growth rate
of 10 percent or more, with the foreign currency reserves
exceeding 140 billion US dollars and other economic indices
hitting record highs. "That is the reason for the stable exchange
rate between the Renminbi and foreign currencies," Salvador said
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese government's efforts to maintain the
stability of the Chinese currency as a contribution to the ongoing
recovery of other Asian economies is highly appreciated by
international society.
</P>
<P>
Rhone-Poulenc, one of the world's biggest chemical companies,
has established six representative offices, 15 joint ventures and
three solely-owned subsidiaries in China since 1992, when the
company initiated a far-reaching investment plan here.
</P>
<P>
Rhone-Poulenc's investment in China so far totals 450 million
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The French company generated 260 million US dollars in sales
revenues in China last year, and the figure is expected to reach
one billion US dollars by 2005.
</P>
<P>
Salvador attributed the success of his China business to the
company's special development strategies which encourage
technology transfer and the localization of products, in addition
to promoting Chinese employees to high management positions.
</P>
<P>
"To win a bigger market share, it is necessary to make more
investment in business entities here," he said.
</P>
<P>
Salvador acknowledged that foreign companies are sometimes
hindered by unequal competition, which is regarded a result of
the country's planned-economy heritage. However, their advantage
in technology and management style will help them to do good
business in China, as the central government is accelerating the
formation of a sound market order in accordance with international
practices, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
