<HEADLINE> Chinese, Finnish Military Leaders Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Gen. Fu Quanyou, chief of the
General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), held
talks with Gen. Gustav Hagglund, commander-in-chief of Finland's
National Defense Forces, here today.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that Hagglund's current China visit is of great
significance to the enhancement of mutual understanding and mutual
trust between the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Having explained China's independent foreign policy of peace,
defense-oriented national defense policy and China's views on the
current international situation, Fu said that China is an staunch
force for safeguarding world peace and stability and will never
pose any threat to any country.
</P>
<P>
Noting that nuclear arms race in south Asia has been caused
entirely by India, he said the nuclear tests conducted by Pakistan
are seen as a response to the threat from India.
</P>
<P>
China expressed deep regrets over Pakistan's nuclear tests and
called on parties concerned to join the Comprehensive Test Ban
Treaty and the Treaty on the Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons
unconditionally and not to take any action which will possibly
worsen the situation in the region, he continued.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of relations between the two countries and their armed
forces, Fu said that the the people of the two countries enjoy a
long history of friendship.
</P>
<P>
There have been more exchanges between the two countries and
two armed forces thanks to the development of bilateral relations,
he added.
</P>
<P>
He told Hagglund that the PLA is ready to advance cooperation
with the Finnish armed forces in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Hagglund said that Finland believes China is a responsible
large country and appreciates China's stand on the Asian financial
crisis and nuclear arms race in south Asia.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Finnish armed forces are ready to
increase exchanges with their Chinese armed forces. He also
briefed Fu on the building of the Finnish armed forces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
