<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The English Football Association
delivered a blow to UEFA President Lennart Johansson as it said on
Friday that it will back FIFA general secretary Sepp Blatter's bid
to become the new president of the world ruling body FIFA at
Monday's Congress.
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman for the English F.A. said that both Blatter and
Johansson, the only two candidates bidding to succeed Joao
Havelange as FIFA president, had been informed of its decision.
</P>
<P>
English F.A. chairman Keith Wiseman explained why they had
given their support to Blatter in a statement issued in London and
faxed to Paris,
</P>
<P>
"A difficult choice has to be made. We believe that as a major
football nation it is our responsibility to make our position
clear in advance, particularly as so many other countries have
expressed interest in our view," said Wiseman.
</P>
<P>
"After careful deliberation, the Football Association is
therefore today announcing that England will cast its vote in
favour of Sepp Blatter."
</P>
<P>
The F.A. decision was a blow to Johansson who was relying on
Europe's support to his presidency bid. 
