<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Drug problem is a global problem,
and Thailand has the same goal as China to eliminate drug abuse,
said Thai Ambassador to China Nikhom Tantemsapya on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks while visiting an on-going anti-drug
exhibition held here yesterday. Nearly 200 foreign diplomats to
China from dozens of countries visited the exhibition, which
opened on May 29.
</P>
<P>
China has already made great progress in banning drugs, which
is a great contribution to the world's anti-drug cause, said a
high-ranking Russian diplomat to China.
</P>
<P>
After watching the exhibition, Dr.Zdzislaw Goralczyk, Polish
Ambassador to China, said that the exhibition was really
impressing, which was both rich in content and of great
significance, and he had a better knowledge of China's efforts in
banning drugs now.
</P>
<P>
Roderic Francis Wye, first Secretary of the British
Embassy in China, said that the youth was vulnerable to drug abuse
because they had scarce knowledge about it. It should be the focus
of all governments around the world to strengthen education on
youth about the harmfulness of drug abuse.
</P>
<P>
With exhibits including more than 1,000 pictures, 100 drug
objects and samples, the exhibition is regarded as the biggest
since the founding of the People's Republic of China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
The month-long exhibition is aimed at increasing people's
awareness of the harmfulness of drugs and deepening the nationwide
anti-drug campaign. 
