<HEADLINE> Song Jian Elected CAE President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- China's leading aerospace expert
Song Jian was elected today president of the Chinese Academy of
Engineering (CAE).
</P>
<P>
Song, also a vice-chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference, led China's anti-ballistic missile
research.
</P>
<P>
The 67-year-old senior engineer, who was the minister in charge
of the former State Commission of Science and Technology, is an
academician of both the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS) and the
CAE.
</P>
<P>
Song studied in the former Soviet Union, and is a foreign
academician of the Academy of Sciences of Russia and the Royal
Swedish Academy of Engineering Sciences.
</P>
<P>
Song is the second president of the CAE, which was established
in 1994, succeeding Zhu Guangya, another of China's leading
aerospace experts.
</P>
<P>
The 439-member CAE is an independent engineering consultative
body paralleling the CAS. 
</P>
</TEXT>
