said, "My mother came here just to attend the ceremony at which I
was awarded with the highest reputation in Chinese scientific
circle.
</P>
<P>
"As early as my childhood, Mother taught me to contribute to the
country and the society," he said, adding that more than half of
the research subjects he is chairing are participated by Chinese
scientists.
</P>
<P>
Professor C.W. Chu, with the University of Houston, said it is
of special significance to be a foreign academician of the CAS,
because it indicates the recognition of his achievement by a
country with a population of 1.2 billion.
</P>
<P>
For a scientist of Chinese descent, it is all the more a
special encouragement and inspiration, Chu said. He also pledged
to promote scientific exchanges between China and the United
States in the future. 
