<HEADLINE> hke060555 -Death Toll From Seasonal Diseases Reaches 295 in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The death toll from seasonal
diseases like gastroenteritis, fever and typhoid has reached 295
by Friday across Nepal, the Department of Health said.
</P>
<P>
At least 28 people have died in the past two days, and most of
them were from Baglung district of western Nepal, the department
said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The death toll may be much higher as figures from the remote
areas of the country are not available yet, it said.
</P>
<P>
The diseases have broken out especially in the underdeveloped
areas of the country, which lack clean drinking water, medicine,
health workers, food and awareness of disease prevention. 
</P>
