<HEADLINE> Macao Unemployment Rate Rises Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate between
February and April this year reached 3.6 percent in Macao, up 0.1
percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
Friday show that the jobless rate was 0.3 percent higher than the
January-March period.
</P>
<P>
The figures were based on sample surveys conducted during the
February and April period by the department.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the under-employment rate was 1.5 percent, up 0.6
percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Macao has been hit by an economic slow-down since 1993. The
economic growth rate for 1997 was estimated less than one percent.
</P>
