<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Korea to Join 6-Nation Marime Military Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 5 (Xinhua) -- South Korea will join a six-nation
combined maritime military manoeuver named "Rim of the Pacific 98",
scheduled for July 8 - August 8 in central Pacific ocean, the Defense
Ministry said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Some 60 warships, a dozen of submarines, 280 planes and more than
30,000 sailors and soldiers from Canada, Chile, Australia, Japan,
South Korea and the United States will join the military exercise.
</P>
<P>
A South Korean flotilla consisted of two frigates, a submarine and
two P3-C antisubmarine surveillance aircraft will depart on June 20
for the military exercise site in the ocean, said a spokesman of the
ministry.
</P>
<P>
The maneuver, which was launched in 1971 and is conducted
biennially since then, is designed to enhance the combined operational
capability of the Pacific-rim nations and provide collective
protection in case of a contingency in the Pacific sea lines of
communication, said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
South Korea began its first participation in the exercise in 1990.
</P>
</TEXT>
