<HEADLINE> World Environment Day Marked in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The message of sustainable
development was echoed by the chief executive; Middle school
campaigners were awarded; Exhibitions on ocean protection are open
to the public -- That's the way Hong Kong commemorated the 26th
World Environment Day Friday.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa said in a message that sustained
development is "consistent with our vision of a forward looking,
dynamic Hong Kong where we place equal emphasis on protection of
our environment and promotion of our economy."
</P>
<P>
Throughout the day, Hong Kong's Environmental Campaign
Committee organized a workshop, featuring lectures on air
pollution, protection of the sea and land, and other aspects.
</P>
<P>
At an awarding ceremony, a training scheme for instructors of
"Scout Environmental Protection Ambassadors," mainly middle school
teachers and students, was launched while prizes were presented to
some schools which have been active in saving the environment.
</P>
<P>
World Environment Day, established by the UN General Assembly
in 1972, aims at raising the public awareness to protect the
environment which is generally degrading worldwide.
</P>
<P>
This year's theme, "For life on Earth: Save Our Seas," honors
the UN International Year of the Ocean. 
</P>
</TEXT>
