<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Paris to Join ``One Day Without Cars'' Activity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Paris will join the ``One Day Without
Cars'' activity to be held on September 22 by the French
Ministry of Environment, said the Mayor of Paris Jean Tiberi on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
But Tiberi said that he preferred a long-term and in-depth plan
to protect environment and fight pollution rather than an
``operation of fist blow.''
</P>
<P>
He said that an in-depth plan could include tipping ``mint
green'' logo on those cars identified as ``clean,'' and suggested
that government officials meet with local community representatives
to discuss anti-pollution measures.
</P>
<P>
On the ``Day Without Cars,'' Paris will have a limited traffic
circulation and commuters will rely on public transport such as
subways, trains, and buses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
