<HEADLINE> 3 Philippine Soldiers Killed in Ambush by Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Three Philippine soldiers were
killed and five others wounded early Friday when a group of
suspected Muslim rebels ambushed a platoon of army troops in a
southern Philippine province, military reports said.
</P>
<P>
The military confirmed that the heavily-armed attackers,
believed to be Muslim rebels, fired from all directions at a
platoon of army troops along a rough road in the village of
Inudaran in Lanao del Norte province.
</P>
<P>
The commander of the platoon was among those killed.
</P>
<P>
The attackers were forced to withdraw when other government
troops went to reinforce the platoon. 
</P>
