<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heart Beepers Help Patients Communicate with Doctors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A beeper that can record the
beatings of a heart, or "telephone transferring electrocardiogram
apparatus" as it is called, has gone into batch production.
</P>
<P>
The small-sized device to the welcome of patients with heart
trouble, provides basic information for doctors to treat these
patients.
</P>
<P>
According to sources at the Chinese Medical Sciences
University, the developer of the device, patients only have to put
three batteries in order and press the switch button when they are
in trouble, and the "beeper" will automatically record the
electrocardiogram of the abnormal heart movement.
</P>
<P>
Then, patients only need to make a phone call to a doctor and
replay the "beeper" so that the doctor can acquire related
information on a computerized network in hospital. Based on the
information obtained and what the patient said, doctors can offer
heart patients prompt advices on how to treat their ailments.
</P>
<P>
The "beeper" is only in the size of a poker card.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
