<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 9:00 GMT, June 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA -- Javier Valle Riestra was sworn in Thursday as Peruvian
Prime Minister to replace Alberto Pandolfi who resigned on the
same day.
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately known why Pandolfi, 57, resigned. Since
becoming prime minister in April 1996, Pandolfi also served as the
fishery minister. (Peru-PM-Resignation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Terry Nichols was sentenced to life in prison
Thursday after refusing to answer questions on how he helped
Timothy McVeigh in the Oklahoma City bombing in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The 43-year-old Nichols was convicted on December 23 of
involuntary manslaughter and conspiracy in the April 19, 1995
bombing that killed 168 people and injured hundreds others.
</P>
<P>
McVeigh, Nichols' Army buddy, was convicted of murder and
conspiracy and sentenced to death last year. (US-Nichols-Life
Imprisonment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. space shuttle Discovery successfully
docked with Russia's Mir orbit station on Thursday afternoon,
completing its ninth and the last hookup in three years with Mir.
</P>
<P>
During its four-day linking with Mir, Discovery will pick up
Andrew Thomas, the seventh and the last American astronaut on the
Russian station, and take back all the science instruments and
experiment samples.
</P>
<P>
Discovery will also present supplies to Mir, including water,
fresh fruit and vegetables. (Shuttle-Docking)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PALERMO, ITALY -- Foreign Ministers from the European Union and
the southern Mediterranean basin ended their two-day informal
meeting Thursday with a commitment to regional cooperation and
security.
</P>
<P>
They said in a statement issued at the end of the meeting that
the process of Euro-Mediterranean integration that was decided
upon at the 1995 Barcelona conference would not be hampered by the
stalled Middle East peace process. (EU-Mediterranean-Foreign
Ministers)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- The International Monetary Fund (IMF) will send a
full team to Indonesia next week to evaluate the continuation of
its aid program following Asia Pacific Director Hubert Neiss's
visit to Jakarta last week, an IMF official said.
</P>
<P>
The IMF had decided to sent a full team for talks with
Indonesian officials about preparations for the second evaluation
of the IMF aid package to the country, head of the IMF
Representative office for Indonesia Kadhim Al-Eyd, said in a press
release on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The team is expected to review the state budget which has
already undergone amendments following the May 13-14 riots and the
replacement of the national leader, said Kadhim. (Indonesia-IMF-Aid)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- The Bosnian Muslim-Croat Federation and the
Republika Srpska (Serb Republic) on Thursday reached an agreement
on clearing land mines.
</P>
<P>
At a Joint Military Committee meeting in Banjaluka, the
U.N. Multinational Stabilization Force (SFOR) agreed to train and
ensure the safety of the mine clearance teams, said Republika
Srpska army chief of staff Momir Talich.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 mine fields containing a total of about 350,000
land mines have been identified across Bosnia. (Bosnia-Mine)  
</P>
