<HEADLINE> S.Korea to Close Six Overseas Embassies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 5 (Xinhua) -- South Korea Friday decided to shut down
its embassies in Belgium, Uruguay, Cameroon, Zambia, Yugoslavia and
Saudi Arabia before September this year.
</P>
<P>
The closures are a part of the South Korean government's
restructuring of its overseas missions, of which, 20 embasssies or
consulates will be shut down before the end of this year due to the
ongoing financial crisis, said a spokesman of the Ministry for
Foreign Affairs and Trade Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ministry will also reduce its diplomat number
abroad, added the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
South Korea, once the 11 largest economy in the world, has been in
serious financial crisis created by corporate failures and bad loans
of financial institutions since late last year, which saw the nation's
per capita income down to 9,000 U.S. dollars from the previous year's
10,548 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
