<HEADLINE> China Construction Bank Improving International Banking System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) - The China Construction Bank (CCB)
will improve its international banking system this year,
computerizing the process to improve competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
A new international settlement system will handle business
electronically, to replace the present system, sending information
through the ALLIANCE system, handling entries, and checking
customers' foreign exchange quotas.
</P>
<P>
The CCB did 50.2 billion US dollars worth of settlements in
1997, or 15.7 percent of the total for Chinese banks, and an
increase of 63.5 percent over the past ten years.
</P>
<P>
The bank expanded the settlement business to 200 branch banks
last year. It is concentrating on settlement business with foreign
companies with large assets, a good credit rating, and
international settlement business.  
