<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Leaded Gas Being Banned In Southwest China Metropolis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 5 (Xinhua) --The Chongqing Municipal Government
recently decided to ban the sale and use of leaded gasoline
beginning July 1 of this year, the municipal government announced
earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing will become the fifth Chinese city in the mainland to
ban the use of leaded gasoline, after Beijing, Tianjin, Shanghai
and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
Because of its topography and climate, Chongqing is known as a
hilly city and for the same reasons, has long ranked high among
cities in China suffering from lead pollution caused by automobile
exhaust.
</P>
<P>
To make sure that unleaded gasoline is used, the municipal
government has told departments to prepare to back up its decision
and anyone who violates the ruling will be penalized, a local
official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
