<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Striving to Improve Investment Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- As a measure to improve investment
environment, the Tianjin Municipal Service Center for Overseas
Investment has announced June as a month of service for overseas
investors.
</P>
<P>
Government officials have been organized to visit
overseas-financed enterprises and help solve problems cropping in
production and business, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
During this month, officials of Customs, commodity
inspection, taxation, labor and personnel departments will be
invited to give lectures and brief overseas investors on the
latest trends of China's investment policies.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin Customs officials have worked out ten measures to
facilitate import of overseas-backed enterprises after they
concluded visits to some of overseas-backed enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Municipal Service Center for Overseas Investment,
founded 11 years ago, consists of officials from various
investment functional departments so that overseas investors can
go through all necessary procedures if they want to start a
venture.
</P>
<P>
As the biggest coastal city in north China, Tianjin is home to
12,000 overseas-financed companies and enterprises, with the
contractual investment amounting to 20 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
