<DOCNO> XIE19980605.0212 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tsunami Hits Eastern DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Tsunami hit the eastern coastal
province of Gangwon in the People's Democratic Republic of Korea
between Tuesday and Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The tidal waves, three to four meters high, brought a railfall
of 170 millimeters and destroyed farmlands and irrigation works,
the Korean Central News Agency (KCNA) reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of casualties yet, but several thousand
hectares of wheat, barley and potato crops in the counties of
Anbyon, Tongcho and Gosong were reported to have been submerged.
</P>
<P>
Rescue operations are continuing and the investigation of
damage is underway, KCNA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
