<HEADLINE> Peru Names New Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Javier Valle Riestra was sworn in
Thursday as Peruvian Prime Minister to replace Alberto Pandolfi
who resigned on the same day.
</P>
<P>
In accepting Pandolfi's resignation, President Alberto Fujimori
"thanked the outgoing minister for his valuable service to the
country, " said a Government Palace statement.
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately known why Pandolfi, 57, resigned. Since
becoming prime minister in April 1996, Pandolfi also served as the
fishery minister.
</P>
<P>
Pandolfi's resignation prompted other ministers in his cabinet
to offer resignations.
</P>
<P>
Javier Valle Riestra, 66, is a lawyer and politician. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
