<HEADLINE>   N.Z. Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A fall in Telecom shares pushed
the New Zealand sharemarket down on Friday after a steady start.
Investors were spooked by a Moody's report that it was reviewing
New Zealand's credit rating.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 16 points lower at 2136 with a turnover
of 145 million dollars (75 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the main leaders, Air New Zealand held steady at 190
cents. Brierley Investment, Carter Holt Harvey and Fletcher
Building gained 1 cent each to 92 cents, 210 cents and 309 cents
separately. Fletcher Energy dropped 3 cents to 542 cents. Lion
Nathan rose 2 cents to 445 cents. Telecom slumped 16 cents to 846
cents and accounted for half of the turnover. 
</P>
</TEXT>
