<HEADLINE> Painting Exhibition Held to Mark World Environment Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of calligraphic works
and paintings opened here today to mark the 26th World Environment
Day.
</P>
<P>
On show are 120 pieces of paintings and 120 calligraphic works
with the theme "for the life on earth", which sing praises of the
beautiful scenery of the country, express the strong hope for a
better environment and criticize acts bringing harm to the
environment.
</P>
