<DOCNO> XIE19980605.0223 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Luo Gan Leaves for UN General Assembly Special Drug-Control Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- State Councillor Luo Gan left here
today at the head of a Chinese delegation for New York to attend
the Special Session of the the United Nations General Assembly on
Drug Control, which is to be held from June 8 to 10.
</P>
<P>
The UN Special Drug Control Session is aimed to cope with the
illicit production, sales, trafficking and distribution of
narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances and related activities.
</P>
<P>
A political declaration is expected to be adopted and six
documents concerning the reduction of drug demand, the fight
against stimulant crimes and money-wash, administration of
drug-susceptible chemicals, judicial cooperation, and psychotropic
substances will be reviewed during the special session.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation comprises officials from the Public
Security Ministry, the Foreign Ministry, the Ministry of Health
and the General Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, after the Drug Control Special Session of the UN
General Assembly is ended, Luo Gan will proceed to lead the
Chinese government delegation on a goodwill visit to Bolivia from
June 10 to 12, at the invitation of the Bolivian government.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the airport to see Luo Gan and his
delegation off were Jia Chunwang, Chinese minister of public
security, Cui Zhanfu, deputy secretary-general of the State
Council, as well as officials of the UN Development Program and of
the Bolivian Embassy in Beijing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
