<DOCNO> XIE19980605.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People Of Shanghai Looking For More Convenience In Life </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 5 (Xinhua) -- As incomes increase China's
leading industrial and commercial city people are spending much
more on culture, information, and entertainment.
</P>
<P>
Spending in this areas was up almost 3-fold over the past five
years, an increase of 3.9 percent annually.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the city's per capita GDP was equal to 3,000 US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Spending on education was in the lead, at 242 yuan (29 US
dollars) in 1997. The 1992 figure was only 35.7 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Spending on telecommunications is also on the rise, with a 1997
figure 82.8 yuan per capita, an almost 3-fold increase from 1992.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, per capita spending on communications
rose at 15.9 percent annually on average. 
</P>
</TEXT>
