<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Ferryboat capsizes, 20 People Missing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Some 20 people were found missing
in a ferryboat accident Thursday morning in the Zhenjiang River of
Chaoguan city in south China's Guangdong province.
</P>
<P>
The seriously over-loaded privately-run ferryboat carried
around 30 people when crossing the river. The boat is designed to
carry only 10 people.
</P>
<P>
The boat capsized in the middle of the river and only 11 people
were rescued by ferryboats nearby.
</P>
<P>
The police and the local port office sent speedboats to search
for the missing immediately after receiving the call for help.
</P>
<P>
Most of the passengers on board were miners.
</P>
<P>
Now the owner of the ferryboat has been arrested by the police
and the accident is under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
