<HEADLINE> Shanghai Company Now Registering Panamanian Ships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Shipping Agency has
been approved by Panama Marine and Trade Service S.A. for
registering Panamanian ships or seamen.
</P>
<P>
The number of Chinese seamen going abroad continues to rise as
the international shipping grows. COSCO's Labor Export Company
sends more than 10,000 seamen abroad annually, mostly on foreign
vessels with Panamanian registry.
</P>
<P>
This registration work was previously handled by Panama and its
representatives in Japan and Hong Kong, but Shanghai Shipping's
new power will make registration and visas more convenient for
Chinese shipping companies and seamen. The Shanghai company can
also help with identity cards, health checkups, and mail service.
</P>
<P>
Panama has the biggest number of ships registered of any
country in the world, at 13,000, with an aggregate tonnage of 110
million DWT.
</P>
<P>
The Panamanian government has an open ship registration policy
and gives preferential treatment in taxation. Some Chinese ships
are registered in Panama. 
</P>
</TEXT>
