<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mirage Observed in Inland City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Many citizens in Chengdu, capital
of southwest China's Sichuan province, were rather excited
Wednesday afternoon as they for the first time in their life saw a
mirage in the city.
</P>
<P>
It was drizzling and cold in the city that day and turned clear
at about 19:00. From 19:30 to 20:45, a mirage appeared on the
northern sky of the city. Witnesses said they could see mountains,
trees and lakes in the mirage.
</P>
<P>
The mirage disappeared at 20:45.
</P>
<P>
Mirage is usually seen in deserts or coastal areas and it is
very rare to be observed in an inland city for it requires special
conditions of sunlight and dusts and water contents in the air,
according to Luo Kesheng, an expert from the Sichuan
Meteorological Observatory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
