<HEADLINE> Marine Cable Hits Land In Southeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The 38,000-km-long Eurasian marine
optical cable hit land at the city of Shantou in south China's
Guangdong Province on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The optical cable starts in Germany, crosses 33 countries and
regions, and has 39 land stations.
</P>
<P>
It has two 20Gb/S optical systems and will be able to carry
480,000 telephone calls at the same time when completed, engineers
say.
</P>
<P>
The land station in Shantou, which covers an area of 2.86
hectares, and other support facilities have been finished. Work on
the land station began in September 1997.
</P>
<P>
The marine cable is expected to be put into service in March
1999. 
</P>
