<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Kenyan Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Kenyan newspapers Friday.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Times:
</P>
<P>
-- Ethiopian and Eritrean troops appeared locked in a fierce
battle for control of disputed territory on their Horn of Africa
border Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Daily Nation:
</P>
<P>
-- Zambian opposition leader and former president Kenneth
Kaunda, in a move that could ease donors' concern about political
stability in Zambia, plans to ask his party next week to release
him from active politics.
</P>
<P>
-- More than 100 Sudanese government troops have been killed
in two days of battles against rebels in the southern Blue Nile
state, the Khartoum government's leading Islamic figure has
admitted.
</P>
<P>
East African Standard:
</P>
<P>
-- At least 17 people were killed and 45 wounded in a fierce
battle between two rival Somali factions in the south-central
town of Baidoa Thursday, a spokesman for one of the groups said.
</P>
