<HEADLINE> 35 Injured as Compressor Exploded in Bangladesh's Garment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- At least 35 female workers of a
garment factory in Bangladesh were injured, five of them
seriously, as a compressor of the factory exploded on Thursday, a
press report said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The compressor of the Young International Garment Factory
exploded with a loud bang at about 4:30 PM in the Chittagong
Export Processing Zone CEPZ), 224 kilometers southeast of here,
due to a power problem, the report quoted fire service sources as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Hearing the loud bang, over 200 female workers of the
two-storied factory rushed through the single staircase, and as a
result, 35 were injured.
</P>
<P>
The critically injured workers were admitted to the CEPZ
medicare center while others were given first aid, the fire
service sources added. 
