<HEADLINE> Northwestern Chinese Province Streamlining Mining Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
has been straightening out the development of its mineral
resources over recent years.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government signed contracts with a host of city
and prefecture governments for the better development of the
mining industry.
</P>
<P>
The province streamlined the structure of coal production in
Lanzhou and Baiyin and closed 24 mines to guarantee safety last
year.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, it closed or suspended production in more than 600
mine pits after discovering 39 illegal mines, and penalized over
4.6 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
A provincial mining bureau official said that Gansu will make
further adjustments in its mining industry, with emphasis placed
on adjusting the exploration of non-ferrous metals, coal, and gold
minerals and in major mining areas like Longnan, Baiyin, and
Lanzhou.  
