<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Tamil Rebels Abduct Young Girls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Tamil rebels of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) abducted 15 young girls
from their homes at Pesalai in the Batticaloa district, Eastern
Province of the country, reports reaching here said Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to reports, about 20 Tigers Wednesday evening entered
the Pesalai hamlet with a list of those to be abducted. They went
to each of those identified houses and took the girls away by
force.
</P>
<P>
The girls are between ages of 15 and 25. The armed LTTE cadres
alleged that they were being taken away for questioning about
their activities for government troops.
</P>
<P>
Some of the girls are reported to have escaped when the LTTE
cadres were confronted by the villagers.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a 15-year war for
independence in the north and east of the country, where the two
million minority Tamils are concentrated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
