<HEADLINE> Agreement on Mine Clearance Reached in Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Bosnian Muslim-Croat
Federation and the Republika Srpska (Serb Republic) on Thursday
reached an agreement on clearing land mines.
</P>
<P>
At a Joint Military Committee meeting in Banjaluka, the
U.N. Multinational Stabilization Force (SFOR) agreed to train and
ensure the safety of the mine clearance teams, said Republika
Srpska army chief of staff Momir Talich.
</P>
<P>
It was also agreed that the three-week training will start on
June 22.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed cooperation between the armed forces of the
Serbs, Muslims and Croats to restore trust among them, Talich
added.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 mine fields containing a total of about 350,000
land mines have been identified across Bosnia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
