<HEADLINE> Russian State Bank to Lower Discount Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Central Bank of the Russian
Federation announced Thursday that the State Bank Committee has
decided to lower the discount rate to 60 percent from Friday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made because of the stabilized domestic
financial market, a Central Bank statement said.
</P>
<P>
In order to settle the financial crisis in late May, the bank
decided on May 27 to lift the discount rate from 50 percent to 150
percent.
</P>
<P>
Premier Sergei Kiriyenko said on Monday that the bank had made
the correct decision, but added that the rate should be lowered
when the financial market was stabilized. 
</P>
