<HEADLINE> China Opening Insurance Sector To Foreign Companies More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- China is making an effort to open
its insurance sector more to foreign companies to have a more
mature and sounder insurance system.
</P>
<P>
The People's Bank of China has given 9 foreign-backed insurance
companies approval to do business in China. Foreign insurance
companies have 181 offices in China.
</P>
<P>
Chinese insurance companies are facing greater competition and
will have to be better prepared for the market competition,
insiders say.
</P>
<P>
Poor performance by China's reinsurance market has affected the
insurance sector's development, according to Shi Jierong, deputy
general manager of the China Pacific Insurance Co., and he says
that some multinational reinsurance and brokerage companies
should be allowed to do business in China.
</P>
<P>
China's insurance companies would then have easier access to
international reinsurance at reduced costs, he adds.
</P>
<P>
The 22 Chinese and foreign insurance companies reported over
100 billion yuan in business last year.
</P>
<P>
Analysts point out that Chinese insurance companies pay little
attention to property insurance, a sector that has great potential
at a time when an increasing number of Chinese families are buying
houses and cars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
