<HEADLINE> Beijing Guaranteeing Basic Livelihood In Rural Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's eastern Chaoyang District
recently set up a basic livelihood system for people in rural
areas with low incomes.
</P>
<P>
It provides permanent rural residents with an average monthly
income of less than 100 yuan (12 US dollars) a basic livelihood
guarantee.
</P>
<P>
District and township governments will cover half the funds
each, and previous temporary relief measures will continue to be
in effect for farmers in need.
</P>
<P>
Chaoyang District has 1.5 million people, approximately 200,000
of them in its suburban rural areas. More than 1,000 persons and
over 500 families are expected to benefit from the new measure.
</P>
</TEXT>
