<DOCNO> XIE19980605.0328 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan's Development Zones Spearhead Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sichuan's development zones generated a total of 40.8 billion
yuan in industrial output value in 1997 and raked in profits
valued at 580 million yuan, according to a provincial official.
</P>
<P>
"These figures indicate that the development zones have become
an important locomotive force for the economic growth of our
province," the official said.
</P>
<P>
He added that Sichuan currently has 50 development zones,
including two state-level ones, and they specialize mainly in new-
and high-technology and the service sector.
</P>
<P>
Incomplete statistics show that the development zones have
invested a total of 57 billion yuan in infrastructure
construction, which includes 48 water plants, 60 power
transmission stations and 30 gas re-distribution stations.
</P>
<P>
Some 8,300 projects had been completed in Sichuan's development
zones by the end of last year, with the total investment hitting
66.6 billion yuan, including 1.2 billion US dollars in paid-in
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
A number of transnational corporations, such as AT&AMP;T,
Motorola, Coca-Cola, Siemens and Fuji, have invested in the
development zones, the official said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
