<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian Seeks Overseas Funds for Forestry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Southeast China's Fujian Province
has already drawn up preferential policies to encourage overseas
investment in local forestry, which is expected to bring in big
economic returns.
</P>
<P>
Fujian is listed among the country's leading provinces in terms
of output of forest products, and has 74 percent of its land area
covered with trees.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors are encouraged to engage in comprehensive
development in mountainous areas, plant subtropical fruit trees,
and fast-growing trees used as industrial raw materials, and
develop the bamboo industry.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors are now allowed to purchase Fujian's
existing forest products-processing enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Bamboo-growing areas in the province exceed 733,000 ha,
leading the country.
</P>
<P>
Fujian now has 473 overseas-funded enterprises involved in the
sector, using 17.9 billion US dollars of contractual overseas
investment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
