<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Beats Slovakia, Advances to Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The United States, hungry to
recapture the world title which it lost in Sydney four years ago,
overcame first-half setbacks to beat Slovakia 89-62 Thursday
night, entering the women's world basketball championship
semifinals.
</P>
<P>
The Americans, silver medalists at last championship, didn't
take a lead until five minutes into action. But some six minutes
later, Slovakia dominated again for a 19-18 lead on Zuzana
Zirkova's three-pointer.
</P>
<P>
The taller and quicker Americans then rallied to take a 41-35
halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
The Slovakians, who placed fifth in last Worlds, made their
best in the second half but lost to the Olympic champions by 27
points.
</P>
<P>
The United States outscored Slovakia with 52 percentage against
35 in the field goal and outrebounded its rival 44-26.
</P>
<P>
Camique Holdsclaw led the United States with 20 points and 13
rebounds. Other five Americans got double-figure points.
</P>
<P>
American center Lisa leslie hit seven points and grabbed five
rebounds in her 20 minutes play.
</P>
<P>
Zuzuna Kamenikova and Alena Kovokova scored 12 points apiece
for Slovakia, followed by Renata Hirakova with 11.
</P>
<P>
The United States faces the winner of Russia-Cuba quarter-final
while Brazil takes on the winner between Australia and Spain.
</P>
<P>
Two other quarterfial games will be played Friday night.
</P>
</TEXT>
