<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Beats Lithuania by Two Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Brazi came closer to its second
straight world crown on Thursday as the defending champion
squeezed past the European champion Lithuania 72-70 in the
quarter-finals of the women's world basketball championship.
</P>
<P>
Brazil opened the game with a 31-21 run but the margin was cut
to six points as two sides walked off the court at 39-33.
</P>
<P>
The second half was a see-saw game which saw Brazil hold off
Lithuanians' strong comeback to clinch a semi-final berth.
</P>
<P>
Lithuania rallied to make it 57-56 on guard Kara Wolters'
three-pointer with 8:22 to play. But the South Americans regained
the control with a 12-5 charge for 68-62 in the last two minutes.
</P>
<P>
Center Alessandra De Oliveira scored 24 points and grabbed 17
rebounds to lead Brazil, while Jurgita Straeimikyte was
Lithuania's scoring leader with 21 points.
</P>
<P>
Brazil will play against the winner between the United States
and Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
The other quarter-final lineup are Russia vs Cuba and Spain
against Australia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
