<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM May Visit Pakistan, India Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina is planning an immediate visit to Pakistan and India in an
effort to defuse tensions between the two South Asian nations.
</P>
<P>
The News Network International quoted an government official as
saying Thursday that "Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina is visiting
Islamabad and New Delhi in order to help defuse tension, which has
been created after the nuclear tests by the two countries."
</P>
<P>
