<DOCNO> XIE19980605.0355 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Education Projects in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Thursday two loans totaling 295.2 million U.S. dollars equivalent
for Mexico's educational development projects.
</P>
<P>
The first loan of 115 million dollars is for a basic education
development project. This project will expand educational
opportunities in initial and basic education for students in the
poorest communities, including indigenous and migrant children,
and improve the quality of basic education for students to achieve
better learning outcomes.
</P>
<P>
The other loan of 180.2 million dollars will be used for
Mexico's higher education finance project. The project will assist
the government in promoting greater equity and quality in the
preparation of university graduates. By increasing access to loans
for qualified and financially needy students, the project will
have a positive impact on the coverage, quality and equity of
higher education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
