<HEADLINE> German Jet Crash Kills One in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A German fighter jet crashed in
Canada's Labrador wilderness Thursday, killing a British airman
aboard and injured a German pilot.
</P>
<P>
The German F4 Phantom crashed and burst into flames moments
after takeoff on a NATO training exercise, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Both men ejected from the small craft into a heavily forested
area.
</P>
<P>
The German pilot walked away with minor scratches and the
British man was found dead at the end of his parachute, with his
helmet knocked off.
</P>
<P>
It was not clear whether the British man's parachute had
malfunctioned, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
A German investigation team was reported to be en route to the
crash site.
</P>
<P>
The F4 Phantom was last built in 1979. About 1,000 of the
aircraft are in use around the world. 
</P>
