<BODY>
<HEADLINE> P5 FM Meeting on South Asia Successful: Tang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The meeting of the five permanent
members of the United Nations Security Council (P5) at the foreign
minister level on the South Asian situation has been remarkably
successful, said Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"It is a good beginning of a new process" to reduce tension in
the region triggered by India, Tang told reporters at the press
conference after the three-hour meeting ended.
</P>
<P>
In May this year, India, in defiance of world opinion, went
ahead with its nuclear tests. After the peace and stability in the
South Asian region was undermined, Pakistan also carried out its
own nuclear tests.
</P>
<P>
During the closed-door meeting, Tang said, the foreign
ministers of China, France, Russia, the United Kingdom and the
United States adopted a joint communique after exchanging views on
the current situation in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
The five realized that they bear important responsibilities
towards world peace and security as the permanent members of the
Security Council, said Tang, who chaired the meeting as China is
the current rotating coordinator of the P5.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese foreign minister said that what has been achieved
at the meeting shows that the P5 are determined to reduce the
tension in South Asia and defend the international
non-proliferation regime through concerted efforts.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that the international community, with international
peace and security facing a severe challenge, should take a common
stand to urge India and Pakistan to stop their nuclear testing
immediately, to abandon their plans of nuclear weaponization and
to sign the Comprehensive Nuclear Test Ban Treaty and the
Non-Proliferation Treaty unconditionally.
</P>
<P>
"A strong and clear message should be given to all countries in
the world that in today's world, any country which attempts to
seek political and military gains by going nuclear will have
nothing to gain but everying to lose," Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He said that peace and security in the South Asian region is
now in grave danger.
</P>
<P>
"The pressing step to the reduction of the tension is for India
and Pakistan to exercise reason and restraint, to resume dialogue
immediately and to look for ways to improve their relations," he
said.
</P>
<P>
At a time when the cold war has been over for years, there is
no other sensible alternative but to settle differences between
states including border disputes by peaceful means, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that all at the meeting are satisfied with what
China, as the current coordinator, has done for the success of the
meeting with support and assistance from the other four.
</P>
<P>
In a world situation changing day by day, Tang said, China will
continue to make its contributions to the protection of peace and
the promotion of development in accordance with its long-standing
peaceful and independent diplomacy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
