<HEADLINE> U.S. Citizens Advised Not to Travel to Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. State Department
Thursday advised American travelers not to travel to Indonesia
despite a decline in violence in the country.
</P>
<P>
The State Department said in a travel warning that violence in
Indonesia has subsided, but the political and economic situation
remains unsettled.
</P>
<P>
